From The economist print edition

Editor in Chief | Bin Chen

Under the tight epidemic situation, all over the reserve shortage of protective materials, requisitioning civilian materials has become a common practice. However, Dali has attracted widespread criticism in recent days for requisitioning control supplies procured by Chongqing and the Hubei Huangshi Epidemic Command.

According to media reports, Dali requisitioned nine masks sent by SF logistics from Ruili to Chongqing, according to an "emergency disposal requisition notice" stamped with the official seal of the city's health bureau.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
And the letter from the Chongqing Epidemic Prevention and Control Leading Group to the Health Bureau of Dali City shows that the masks were purchased by enterprises designated by the Chongqing Epidemic Prevention and control headquarters. Another letter from the Huangshi Defense and Control Command to the Dali Bai Autonomous Prefecture Defense and Control Command, the Huangshi Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters commissioned the Western business department of Huaxin Cement, a leading local enterprise, and the Chongqing Huangshi Chamber of Commerce Enterprise (Chongqing Qiaodu pharmaceutical company) to purchase a batch of materials, which were then shipped through the Dali Branch of Shunfeng Company, it was sent from Ruili to Huangshi, but it was also detained in Dali.

Ruili is a border city, and the materials may have been bought from outside the country by companies entrusted with them, which pass through Ruili and into the country. In fact, the news that supplies donated by foreign countries to Hubei have been forcibly commandeered by the local customs authorities has also been reported repeatedly on social media.

According to the Emergency Response Law, the relevant government and its departments may requisition the property of units and individuals in response to emergencies. However, according to the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases and the need for the control of infectious diseases, local governments have the right to urgently mobilize personnel or reserve materials within their respective administrative areas, temporary requisition of houses, means of transport and related facilities and equipment. It is the jurisdiction of the State Council to mobilize personnel and materials throughout the country or across provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the central government. The ownership of the protective materials purchased by enterprises entrusted by the epidemic prevention and control headquarters of Chongqing and Huangshi belongs to these two cities. The Dali Branch of SF express is only the carrier, not the owner of the related materials, and Dali has no right to levy them across provinces.

In terms of the severity of the outbreak, Huangshi is under the jurisdiction of Hubei Province, less than 100 km from Wuhan, making it one of the worst affected areas. Chongqing also borders Hubei Province. As of February 5, there were 566 confirmed cases in Huangshi, 389 in Chongqing and only eight in Dali. The situation of epidemic prevention and control in these two places is undoubtedly more severe. The withholding and collection of urgently procured protective materials by Dali will have a significant impact on the prevention and control of the epidemic in both places.

The State Council General Office issued an emergency notice as early as January 29, it is proposed that the key medical emergency prevention and control materials produced by local enterprises, such as medical protective clothing, N95 face masks, medical goggles, negative pressure ambulances and related drugs, should be under the unified management and unified allocation of the material support group of the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council in response to the epidemic situation of new pneumonia, local Government of the People's Republic of China at all levels shall not intercept and call in any name. At a meeting of the Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China on Feb. 3, Xi pointed out that the prevention and control of the epidemic should stick to a national chess game. Party committees and governments at all levels must firmly obey the unified command, unified coordination and unified dispatch of the Party Central Committee and carry out orders and prohibitions. All regions and departments must strengthen the overall situation awareness and overall concept, firmly obey the command of the Central Leading Group to respond to the epidemic situation and the joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council. The measures taken by various departments in different regions should take into account not only the needs of prevention and control in their respective areas, but also the impact on key areas and on national prevention and control.

Dali provided 30,000 masks to the Dali Bai Autonomous Prefecture Real Estate Association, according to a press release issued shortly after. China National Association (Property Association) and the Provincial Housing Association also provided 10,000 masks to Dali, "temporarily easing the demand for masks. ". Even health care workers are facing a shortage of protective equipment in areas where the epidemic is intense, such as Hubei and Chongqing, while Dali, which has only eight confirmed cases, has seized urgently needed supplies ahead of it, while at the same time providing a large number of face masks to the real estate associations of higher-level governments, not In line with the central provisions, the overall national response to the epidemic ineffective.

On the 5th, Dali said in an interview with the media that the materials had been distributed and could not be recovered. Fortunately, after public opinion fermentation, 6, Chongqing Commerce Committee said that Dali has "promised to return the mask. ".

On the afternoon of February 6, the headquarters of the Leading Group for the response to the epidemic in Yunnan Province criticized the requisition of epidemic prevention and control materials by the Dali City Government in Dali Bai Autonomous Prefecture and the Dali Health Bureau, and ordered the immediate return of the requisitioned materials. The circular demanded that all departments throughout the province should take this as a warning, draw lessons from it, pay attention to politics and the overall situation, and never allow similar incidents to happen again. If they do, they will be seriously held accountable.

On the same day, the Dali headquarters for the COVID-19 of pneumonia also responded, "we sincerely apologize to all parties in the community for the temporary withholding of face masks in the early stage, and have conducted a deep reflection and review on the impact caused. " The relevant personnel will be dealt with seriously and all parties are kindly requested to give their understanding. For the masks that are temporarily withheld but not yet used, those that can be returned will all be returned to the subject of requisition; for those that can not be returned after they have been used, timely compensation will be given to those that can not be returned after they have reached a paid collection agreement through communication; and for those that have been used but can not be returned, and the subject of the Levy needs masks, will be returned as soon as possible after completion.

The Dali side should fulfill its commitment as soon as possible to allow the shortage of materials to play a role in the most urgent areas as soon as possible.

Such practices must be investigated and dealt with as an example to others. Otherwise, if the local governments are random collection of control materials passing through the area, will be on the national anti-epidemic a chess game to bring serious damage.
